# Q4: NotebookLM Evaluation - Experiment Log
## BUS5001 Assessment 3 - Tabassum Tanzim Nawar

## Notebook Title
ESG Reporting Standards Briefing

## Scenario
Preparing a student briefing on ESG reporting standards 
for a governance and compliance workshop.

## Sources Used
1. GRI - How to use the GRI Standards
   URL: https://www.globalreporting.org/how-to-use-the-gri-standards/

2. IFRS - International Sustainability Standards Board (ISSB)
   URL: https://www.ifrs.org/groups/international-sustainability-standards-board/

3. Climate Change - United Nations
   URL: https://www.un.org/en/climatechange

## Features Evaluated
1. Conversational Q&A with source citations
2. Audio Overview
3. Mind Map
4. Quiz

## Queries Used for Q&A Testing
Query 1: What are the key principles of ESG reporting 
standards and why are they important for organisations?

Query 2: How should an organisation measure and report 
on its carbon emissions under current ESG frameworks?

## Key Observations
- All three sources loaded successfully
- Q&A responses included numbered source citations
- Audio Overview generated a conversational dialogue 
  summarising all three sources
- Mind Map organised ESG concepts into a visual hierarchy
- Quiz generated questions based on source content
- Responses grounded in uploaded sources rather than 
  general knowledge

